Cases in various countries not mentioned above or more recent case numbers.

Caribbean locally acquired
---
Caymans. 27 Nov 2014. (reported) 60 cases, (conf.) 36 cases.
http://www.cayman27.com.ky/2014/11/27/latest-chikungunya-figures-released

Dominican Republic. 3 Dec 2014. As of 8 Nov 2014, Week 45 (susp.) 524 297 cases, 2275 cases during last week.
http://digepisalud.gob.do/boletines/boletines-semanales/cat_view/34-boletines-semanales/129-noviembre-2014.html [in Spanish]

St. Martin. 24 Nov 2014. Estimated seroprevalence 16.9 (12-20) per cent of the population; Prevalence of mild or asymptomatic cases 40 per cent of all cases.
http://www.invs.sante.fr/Publications-et-outils/Bulletin-de-veille-sanitaire/Tous-les-numeros/Antilles-Guyane/Bulletin-de-veille-sanitaire-Antilles-Guyane.-n-3-4-5-Septembre-Novembre-2014 [in French]

Turks and Caicos. 2 Dec 2014. (susp.) 197 cases, (conf.) 19 cases.
http://tcweeklynews.com/nearly-catch-mosquito-viruses-this-year-p5682-127.htm

USA Virgin Islands. 2 Dec 2014. (susp.) 1392 cases; Deaths 1; Islands affected: St. Croix (susp.) 374 cases, (conf./probable) 12 cases, St. Thomas (susp.) 857 cases, (conf./probable) 102 cases, St. John (susp.) 41 cases, (conf./probable) 41 cases.
http://stcroixsource.com/content/news/local-news/2014/12/02/st-croix-peak-chikungunya-outbreak-st-thomas-cases-decline

Mexico and Central America probable local transmission
---
Mexico (Chiapas state). 1 Dec 2014. (conf.) 39 cases [25 of the new cases are presumably locally acquired].
http://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/2014/12/01/995303 [in Spanish]

