[2] Patient management
Date: Sun 30 Nov 2014
From: Fabrice Simon <simon-f@wanadoo.fr> [edited]


To adequately manage the chikungunya [virus]-infected patients in the current outbreak in the French Caribbean islands and in French Guiana, the French Ministry of Health (Direction Generale de la Sante) asked the Societe de Pathologie Infectieuse de Langue Francaise to propose guidelines for case management at all stages. The work was conducted with some other societies (rheumatologists, general practitioners, rehabilitation) and the national reference center for arboviral diseases.

These guidelines are now available in French at :
http://www.infectiologie.com/site/_actualite_detail.php?id_actualite=455

An English version of these guidelines will be available in the coming weeks.

--
Pr Fabrice Simon, MD, PhD
Department of Infectious Diseases and Tropical Medicine Laveran Military Teaching Hospital
Marseille, France
<simon-f@wanadoo.fr>

[ProMED thanks Dr. Simon for sending in the link to the guidelines. Having a version in English will be very helpful for patient treatment. One hopes that versions in Spanish and in Portuguese will follow quickly as well. - Mod.TY]

